I&nbsp;got lovely food poisonig today after a horrible week at work.&nbsp; We had two visits from regional managers on tuesday and thursday.&nbsp; My boss has been out for a week, so the bakery wasn;t functionig properly without its manager.&nbsp; We had our supervisor, but he was out both of those days.&nbsp;&nbsp;Guess who was the only one running the bakery while the regionals were in.. ME.&nbsp; Everyones shortcomings all week fell back onto me.&nbsp; I&nbsp;really feel like it made me look like a terrible employee.&nbsp; I didn't take one break all week, which gets me into trouble with the union if they find out. &nbsp;I also ended up workin a lot of overtime.&nbsp; I really hope the my boss comes back and realizes how much Tara and I busted our asses trying to make everything run smoothly.&nbsp; 

So I worked monday-friday, which is bizzare, because that means that I have off Saturday and Sunday.&nbsp; I'm not complaing at all about that.&nbsp; The only thing that really sucks is that I come home and PUKE&nbsp;my brains out.&nbsp; 


I really wish that I could call Fred.&nbsp;

I&nbsp;DID&nbsp;NOTHING&nbsp;TODAY. not ONE thing.

Actually, that is not technically correct.&nbsp; Today I did not move out of my bed for about four and a half hours.&nbsp; I&nbsp;did cook breakfast, go to wendys, take a shower, read.&nbsp; BUT majority of my time was spent on the internet.&nbsp; The thing is yesterday I had big plans in my head to really really really clean my room and go get Danny Boi a bday prez.&nbsp;

As I sat on my bed I&nbsp;thought to myself &quot;I really need to move. I really need to go do what I have to get done today because tomorrow I have work and I will never accomplish it all.&quot; And it was like being stuck in cement in my own mind.&nbsp; I&nbsp;knew I had to do something but my brain would not produce the motor function of extending my legs off the corner of my bed into the direction of productivity.&nbsp; 

Caitlin Elizabeth Steele today you FAIL.
